<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>yonolog</title><link href="../." rel="alternate"></link><link href=".././feeds/all.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>../.</id><updated>2011-07-02T20:50:27Z</updated><entry><title>Export PDF from Redmine's Wiki</title><link href=".././export-pdf-from-redmines-wiki.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2011-07-02T20:50:27Z</updated><author><name>Yusaku ONO</name></author><id>tag:None,2011-07-02:.././export-pdf-from-redmines-wiki.html/</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;I'll introduce a Redmine's plugin, &lt;a href="http://www.redmine.org/plugins/redmine_doc_pu"&gt;DocPu&lt;/a&gt;.
It's enable us to export PDF from Redmine's Wiki.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I tried to set up the plugin on Debian Squeeze.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Install LaTeX packages.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DocPu uses LaTeX environment, so we must install LaTeX packages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I installed these packages using aptitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ptex-bin&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ptex-buildsupport&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ptex-jtex&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;texlive-latex-recommended&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;texlive-latex-extra&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;cjk-latex&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;latex-cjk-japanese&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;latex-cjk-japanese-wadalab&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Install DocPu&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Download and locate the plugin's directory to $RAILSROOT/vendor/plugins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="codehilite"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;wget&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;http:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;//&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;www&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;redmine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;org&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/attachments/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;4975&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;redmine_doc_pu_v003&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;zip&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;unzip&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;redmine_doc_pu_v003&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;zip&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;mv&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;redmine_doc_pu&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;$RAILSROOT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/vendor/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;plugins&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;sudo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="sr"&gt;/etc/i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;nit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;d&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;apache2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;restart&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;After that, you should see the plugin's item in above menu [Administration] -&amp;gt; [Plugin].&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Customize a template&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Default templates doesn't include Japanese version.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I wrote a template based on artile_en_tcfi.tex (one of the default templates).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="codehilite"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# diff article_ja_tcfi.tex article_en_tcfi.tex&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="mi"&gt;21&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;d20&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;usepackage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;CJKutf8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="mi"&gt;38&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;d36&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;CJK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;UTF8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;min&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="mi"&gt;54&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;d51&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;CJK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h2&gt;Export PDF&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I refered to &lt;a href="http://www.redmine.org/plugins/redmine_doc_pu"&gt;the documentation&lt;/a&gt; for making PDF.&lt;/p&gt;</summary></entry><entry><title>Studying with CodeEval</title><link href=".././studying-with-codeeval.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2011-06-15T00:55:05Z</updated><author><name>Yusaku ONO</name></author><id>tag:None,2011-06-15:.././studying-with-codeeval.html/</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;I installed Pelican as a environment to write a blog much easier.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="codehilite"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;% mkvirtualenv pelican&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;% pip install pelican&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;% mkdir content &amp;amp;&amp;amp; cd content&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;% vim hoge.md&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;% pelican ~/content&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary></entry><entry><title>Translating MAHALO License</title><link href=".././translating-mahalo-license.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2011-06-13T00:05:01Z</updated><author><name>Yusaku ONO</name></author><id>tag:None,2011-06-13:.././translating-mahalo-license.html/</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/gongo/Tython/blob/development/LICENSE"&gt;MAHALO License&lt;/a&gt; is a software license defined by
&lt;a href="http://twitter.com/gongoZ"&gt;@gongoZ&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;@gongoZ is a developer of the &lt;a href="http://d.hatena.ne.jp/gongoZ/20110514/1305372647"&gt;Tython programming language&lt;/a&gt;.
He distributes Tython with the MAHALO License.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MAHALO License is based on MIT License and is added the below sentence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ソフトウェアを使用する際、(ソフトウェアに限らず)何かに対して「感謝」をすることとします。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I'm trying to translate this sentence into English.
It's a draft version.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You shall thank for anyone (not only to the software) when you use the software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</summary></entry><entry><title>Publish the blog created by Pelican at github</title><link href=".././publish-the-blog-created-by-pelican-at-github.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2011-06-11T18:20:54Z</updated><author><name>Yusaku ONO</name></author><id>tag:None,2011-06-11:.././publish-the-blog-created-by-pelican-at-github.html/</id><summary type="html">&lt;div class="codehilite"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;mkdir&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;p&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/.pelican/co&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ntent&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;vim&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/.pelican/s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;etting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;py&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;cat&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/.pelican/s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;etting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;py&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="c1"&gt;#!/usr/bin/env python&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="n"&gt;OUTPUT_PATH&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;/path/to/github/site/repository/blog/&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;vim&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/.pelican/co&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ntent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hoge&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;md&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/.pelican/s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;etting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;py&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;~&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/.pelican/co&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ntent&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="sr"&gt;/path/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/github/si&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;te&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/repository/&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;git&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;git&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;commit&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;add blog by pelican&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nv"&gt;git&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;push&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;origin&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;master&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It may be better to write a script for automation creating blog and deploying.&lt;/p&gt;</summary></entry><entry><title>Install Pelican with virtualenvwrapper</title><link href=".././install-pelican-with-virtualenvwrapper.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2011-06-06T00:00:00Z</updated><author><name>Yusaku ONO</name></author><id>tag:None,2011-06-06:.././install-pelican-with-virtualenvwrapper.html/</id><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;I installed Pelican as a environment to write a blog much easier.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="codehilite"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;% mkvirtualenv pelican&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;% pip install pelican&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;% mkdir content &amp;amp;&amp;amp; cd content&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;% vim hoge.md&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pelican&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;% pelican ~/content&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary></entry></feed>